tion-focused urban development. The spatial and sometimes even organizational merging of libraries, adult educations centers, and other institutions has not yet been addressed in scholarship. This volume looks at 10-15 examples to present their development and offerings, organizational and spatial structures, and concepts of collaboration.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aKommune. 4aKulturzentrum. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Library & Information Science / School Media.2bisacsh  aCultural center.  amunicipality.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Library and Information Science 2023z9783111318233oZDB-23-DGB0 cEPUBz97831104978090 cprintz978311050042440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110501117zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110501117zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110501117/original  a978-3-11-117578-2 DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGBb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-GOA